  "text": "That's a wrap! EuroPython Beginners' Day Unconference is behind us and it's been a blast.\n\nTogether with Honza Javorek and Junior Guru I wanted to thank everyone who made this event possible:\n\n➡️ The EuroPython 2025 Conference, EuroPython Society and in particular Mia Bajić and Artur Czepiel for the idea and recruiting us to make it all happen\n➡️ Anezka Muller and Jodie Burchell, PhD for making the event a reality\n➡️ Emilia Stelmasiak for assisting with research, content and digital assets\n➡️ Our fantastic panelists Jana Moudrá, Michaela Trčková, Gábor Ambrózy, Manivannan Selvaraj, Šimon Kořený, Miloslav Ježek, Václav Kotyk as well as the brave Ella Michaela Malečková, without you all this wouldn’t have happened\n➡️ Volunteers of EuroPython who have tirelessly worked on preparing the venue and making sure everything ran smoothly, and who create this amazingly supportive & caring environment in which people feel great.\n\nLast but not least, huge thanks to the audience. We greatly appreciated your presence, energy and curiosity. Each and every lightning talk was fantastic, your participation in the workshop was really great. We still can’t believe that so many of you decided to join us on a Saturday in July, and spend 9 hours learning, sharing and connecting.\n\nThe photos below show how Honza & myself felt before and after the Unconference.\n\n#EuroPython #BeginnersDay #Unconference",
